    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>parsnip[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into quarters</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife</p><p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a deep baking tray (or two!) with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped parsnip</strong>,<strong> onion wedges</strong>, <strong>trimmed</strong> <strong>green beans </strong>and<strong> crushed garlic</strong></p><p>Add a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>dried thyme </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Nestle the green beans underneath the other veg as much as you can to prevent them burning!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken</strong> to the tray[s], nestled amongst the veg</p><p>Top the chicken with the <strong>remaining dried thyme</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the veg is golden and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>gravy base</strong> to a heatproof measuring jug with your<strong> onion marmalade</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Put it in the <strong>microwave </strong>and cook for 1 min or until thickened</p><p>Give everything a good mix up (careful it may be hot!) \u2013 this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tray bake is cooked, remove from the oven</p><p>Carefully remove the skin from the <strong>garlic</strong> (it will be hot!)</p><p>Return the <strong>roasted garlic</strong> to the tray[s] and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>roast chicken & root veg tray bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roast-chicken-thigh-and-root-veg-tray-bake-with-onion-gravy/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> roast chicken & root veg tray bake</strong> with the <strong>onion gravy </strong>drizzled all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
